This paper is about keyphrase generation, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model called Title-Guided Network (TG-Net) for automatic keyphrase generation task based on the encoder-decoder architecture with two new features. This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing, which is the main focus of this paper. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): Keyphrase generation is a task related to information retrieval, which is covered in this sub-category. 
- cs.LG (Learning): The paper proposes a new model based on the encoder-decoder architecture with two new features, which is related to machine learning and deep learning, covered in this sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Keyphrase generation is a task related to artificial intelligence, which is covered in this sub-category. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed model is based on the encoder-decoder architecture with two new features, which is related to neural networks, covered in this sub-category.
